(vii) The Central Government through the Department of Agriculture Cooperation and Farmers Welfare shall also contribute an equal amount as contributed by the eligible subscriber, to the pension Fund. Account of such co-contributions shall be maintained separately by the LIC and these co-contributions along with fund earnings from time to time shall be utilized for pension payment on the date of vesting. Co-contributions would not be paid to subscribers in case of pre-mature exits. In such a case, the co-contributions along with fund earnings will be transferred back to Pension Fund.
